--
A database is an organized collection of structured information, or data, typically stored
electronically in a computer system. A database is usually controlled by a database management system (DBMS).
--

Types of Database :-
1. Hierarchical Databases
2. Relational Databases
3. Non-Relational Databases
4. Object oriented databases

--

Relational Database (RDBMS) :-
A relational database is a way of structuring information in tables, rows, and columns.
An RDB has the ability to establish links—or relationships–between information by joining tables,
which makes it easy to understand and gain insights about the relationship between various data points.

--

SQL :-
Structured Query Language (SQL) is a programming language used to extract, organize,
manage, and manipulate data stored in relational databases.

